Background

		Mr. Alan M. Bennett served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of H&R Block Management, LLC. Mr. Bennett served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of H&R Block, Inc. from July 2010 to May 16, 2011. He served as the Chief Financial Officer, Senior Vice President and Controller of Aetna Inc., an affiliate of Aetna Services Inc. from September 28, 2001 to 2007. He served as Vice President and Corporate Controller of Aetna Inc. from December 2000 to November ... 2001. He served as interim Chief Executive Officer of H&R Block, Inc. from November 2007 to August 2008. He served as Vice President and Corporate Controller of former Aetna since March 1998 and served as Vice President and Director of Internal Audit from March 1997 to March 1998 and as the Chief Financial Officer of Aetna Business Resources from July 1995 to March 1997. Before joining Aetna, he held several executive positions with Pirelli Armstrong Tire Corporation. Mr. Bennett was responsible for all sales and marketing of Bausch & Lomb Inc.'s products for North America, Canada, Mexico and the Caribbean and served as Vice President and General Manager of Bausch & Lomb Inc.'s 62 retail truck, tire and battery centers located in 32 states, before undertaking progressively more senior assignments within Bausch & Lomb Inc.'s finance organization. From 1972 to 1981, he served as an Audit Manager at Ernst & Young and was responsible for all aspects of planning, staffing and executing audit, tax and internal accounting control evaluations for a wide variety of clients. He has been an Independent Directorate Fluor Corporation (also know as Cibolo Creek Infrastructure JV) since November 4, 2011. He has been an Independent Director at Halliburton Company since May 17, 2006 and The TJX Companies, Inc. since September 14, 2007. He served as a Member of the Board of Directors at H&R Block Management, LLC. He served as a Director of H&R Block, Inc. from 2008 to September 2011 and Bausch & Lomb Incorporated from March 2004 to 2008. He is on the Committee on Corporate Reporting of the Financial Executives Institute, Director of Gaylord Hospital, a Member of the Accounting Advisory Board of the University of Connecticut, a former Trustee of the Connecticut Policy and Economic Council, a Member and Past President of the New Haven Lions Club and is a Member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants and the Connecticut Society of Certified Public Accountants. Mr. Bennett graduated from Susquehanna University in Selinsgrove, Pennsylvania in 1972 and holds a B.S. degree in Accounting. He is a Certified Public Accountant.Read Full Background




