About Bennett Metal Products, Inc.




Bennett Metal Products, Inc. is a second-generation, family-owned, ISO-certified shop offering multi-axis CNC precision milling and turning, product prototyping, mechanical and electrical assembly, welding, waterjet cutting, conventional machining, short-run production, tool & die building, and testing. 




Jim Bennett, a die maker with many years’ experience, established Bennett Metal Products, Inc. in 1969. He built the business on the foundation of hard work, integrity, and honesty. Over the last five decades, Bennett Metal Products, Inc. has been committed to becoming one of the finest precision job shops in the Midwest. We have experienced continuous and steady growth. Our around the clock operation, combined with our central location and access to major interstate and trucking lines, enables us to ship products quickly and economically anywhere in the Continental United States.




One of the finest precision job shops in the Midwest




We invest in the latest technology and equipment, retain the highest-quality people, and provide customers with top-quality products and services at a fair price. We provide exceptional project management to assist our customers in reducing costs and improving the life of their equipment and products. 


 


Contact us to obtain more information or to request a quote.




Improve your product's quality while reducing the costs of fabrication and assembly







